 is the author’s purpose of writing the passage?","textExplain":"定位：由题干中的the author’s purpose可知本题考查作者的写作目的，属于主旨题。\n解析：全文中作者一直在强调美国需要学习中国人的勤俭，文章最后一句说，If Americans saved more and spent less, consistently over time, they wouldn’t have to worry about all that，“如果美国人多存钱少花钱，久而久之，就不会有那样的担忧了”。即作者希望美国政府减少借债，降低赤字，故A选项为正确答案。","videoExplainUrl":"","rightOpt":1,"userOpt":0,"answerJsons":[{"option":1,"content":"To urge the American government to cut deficits."},{"option":2,"content":"To encourage Chinese people to spend more."},{"option":3,"content":"To tell Americans not to worry about their economy."},{"option":4,"content":"To promote understanding between China and America."}]}]},{"id":5016,"name":"2012.12 (Passage One 卷二)","content":"    Who’s poor in America? That’s  a question hard to answer. Hard because there’s no conclusive definition of poverty. Low income matters, though how low is unclear. Poverty is also a state of mind that fosters self-defeating behavior—bad work habits, family breakdowns, and additions. Finally, poverty results from bad luck: accidents, job losses, disability.\n    Despite poverty’s messiness, we’ve measured progress against it by a single statics: the federal poverty line. By this measure, we haven’t made much progress. But the apparent lack of progress is misleading for two reasons.\n    First, it ignores immigration. Many immigrants are poor and low skilled. They add to the poor. From 1989 to 2007, about three quarters of the increase in the poverty population occurred among Hispanics(西班牙裔美国人)—mostly immigrants and their children.\n    Second, the poor’s material well-being has improved. The official poverty measure obscures this by counting only pre-tax cash income and ignoring other sources of support, including food stamps and housing subsidies. Although many poor live from hand to mouth, they’ve participated in rising living standards. In 2005, 91% had microwaves, 79% air-conditioning, and 48% cell phones.\n    The existing poverty line could be improved by adding some income resource and subtracting some expenses. Unfortunately, the administration’s proposal for a “supplemental poverty measures” in 2011 goes beyond that. The new poverty number would compound public confusion. It also raises questions about whether the statics is tailored to favor a political agenda.\n    The “supplemental measures” ties the poverty threshold to what the poorest third of Americans spend on food, housing, clothing, and utilities. The actual threshold will probably be higher than today’s poverty line. Many Americans would find this weird: people get richer, but “poverty”stays stuck.\n    What produces this outcome is a different view of poverty. The present concept is an absolute one: the poverty threshold reflects the amount estimated to meet basic needs. By contrast, the new measure embraces a relative notion of poverty: people are automatically poor if they’re given distance from the top, even if their income are increasing.\n    The new indicator is a “propaganda device” to promote income redistribution by showing that poverty is stubborn or increasing. The Census Bureau has estimated statics similar to the administration’s proposal. In 2008, the traditional poverty rate was 13.2%; estimates of the new statics range up to 17%. The new poverty statistic exceeds the old, and the gap grows larger over time.\n    As senator Daniel Moynihan said, the administration is defining poverty up. It’s legitimate to debate how much we should aid the poor or reduce economic inequality. But the debate should not be swayed by misleading statistics that few Americans could possibly understand. Government statistics should strive for political neutrality(中立). This one fails.","audioUrl":"","questionJson":[{"id":103025,"title":"What is the main idea of the first paragraph?","textExplain":"定位：由题干中的the first paragraph定位至文章首段。\n解析：文章第一段第三句说Hard because there’s no conclusive definition of poverty，“因为贫困没有明确的定义，所以很难回答什么是贫困”。接下来的三句分别从收入高低、心理状态和运气好坏三个方面来解释为什么贫困难以界定。由此可知，第一段的中心意思是说大家在贫困的定义上没有达成共识。故D选项为正确答案。","videoExplainUrl":"","rightOpt":4,"userOpt":0,"answerJsons":[{"option":1,"content":"Poverty is very often defined as a state of mind."},{"option":2,"content":"Poverty is a problem hard to tackle in America."},{"option":3,"content":"Bad work habits and bad luck lead to poverty."},{"option":4,"content":"There is no consensus on the concept of poverty."}]},{"id":103026,"title":"What does the author say about the poor in America?","textExplain":"定位：由题干中的the poor定位到文中第四段第一句。\n解析： 定位句说Second, the poor’s material well-being has improved，“穷人的物质生活已经得到改善”，可知穷人的生活水平提高了，故A选项为正确答案。","videoExplainUrl":"","rightOpt":1,"userOpt":0,"answerJsons":[{"option":1,"content":"Their living standards have actually improved."},{"option":2,"content":"Most of them are immigrants and their descendants."},{"option":3,"content":"Their chances of rising above the poverty line are slim."},{"option":4,"content":"Most of them rely on government subsidies for survival."}]},{"id":103027,"title":"What does the author think of administration’s proposal for a “supplemental poverty measure”?","textExplain":"定位：根据题干的supplemental poverty measures定位到文章第五段第二句。\n解析：定位句说政府提出的贫困补充措施提高了贫困线的门槛。第五段最后一句说，It also raises questions about whether the statics is tailored to favor a political agenda，“人们质疑该措施是为了支持某一政治议程而量身定做”。也就是说这一标准可能是为某种政治目服务的，故B选项为正确答案。","videoExplainUrl":"","rightOpt":2,"userOpt":0,"answerJsons":[{"option":1,"content":"It is intended to further help the poor."},{"option":2,"content":"It is made to serve political purposes."},{"option":3,"content":"It is a positive response to changed circumstances."},{"option":4,"content":"It is an attempt to combat the economic recession."}]},{"id":103028,"title":"What is the characteristics of the new measure of poverty?","textExplain":"定位：由题干中的characteristic 和new measure定位到文章第七段最后一句。\n解析：定位句指出，the new measure embraces a relative notion of poverty: people are automatically poor if they’re given distance